io.github.samwright.framework.model.common

Interface Versioned

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Element, Processor, TopProcessor, Workflow, WorkflowContainer
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractElement, AbstractProcessor, AbstractWorkflow, AbstractWorkflowContainer, Adder, ChooserWorkflowContainer, ContourFinder, ExContainer, FingertipFinder, FingertipReducer, HandDetector, ImageLoader, KeyboardActor, MockElement, NNClassifier, Optimiser, PalmDetector, SimplifyContour, SkinDetector, SplitJoinWorkflowContainer, StartElement, StaticColourRange, TopWorkflowContainer, Viewer, WorkflowImpl

    public interface Versioned
    Each EventuallyImmutable object has one VersionInfo object which describes tracks its earlier and later versions.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void discardNext()
      Discards any replacement to this object and ensures this object is not deleted, therefore allowing for it to be replaced by another Replaceable object.
      void discardPrevious()
      Discard older versions of this, so they may be freed by the garbage collector.
      Versioned getCurrentVersion()
      Returns the current version of this object.
      Versioned getNext()
      Gets the next version of the EventuallyImmutable object.

      Gets the previous version of the EventuallyImmutable object.
      UUID getUUID()
      Gets the universally unique identifier for this object.
      void setAsCurrentVersion()
      Sets this object as the current version (along with objects associated with it), informing all relevant controllers and registers to the change.

      Sets the universally unique identifier for this object (and all future versions of this).

    • Method Detail

      • getNext

        Versioned getNext()
        Gets the next version of the EventuallyImmutable object. If this describes the latest version, the method returns null.
        Returns:
        the next version of the EventuallyImmutable object.

      • getPrevious

        Versioned getPrevious()
        Gets the previous version of the EventuallyImmutable object. If this describes the earliest (ie. first) version, the method returns null.
        Returns:
        the previous version of the EventuallyImmutable object.

      • discardNext

        void discardNext()
        Discards any replacement to this object and ensures this object is not deleted, therefore allowing for it to be replaced by another Replaceable object. In doing so, it makes the next version discard its previous version.

      • discardPrevious

        void discardPrevious()
        Discard older versions of this, so they may be freed by the garbage collector. In doing so it makes the previous version discard its next version.

      • setUUID

        void setUUID(UUID uuid)
        Sets the universally unique identifier for this object (and all future versions of this).

        No checks for uniqueness are performed.

        Parameters:
        uuid - the universally unique identifier to set for this object.

      • getUUID

        UUID getUUID()
        Gets the universally unique identifier for this object.

      • setAsCurrentVersion

        void setAsCurrentVersion()
        Sets this object as the current version (along with objects associated with it), informing all relevant controllers and registers to the change.

      • getCurrentVersion

        Versioned getCurrentVersion()
        Returns the current version of this object.
        Returns:
        the current version of this object.
